		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>thanks for reexplaining that to everyone. Just a little comment this isnt "the big secret" since you can read it on many sites on the net :-)<br>I can add a few things you didnt mention that could help people level faster. First of all there s a "xp owner", the guy who gets the xp. Usually it s the guy who did most damages. Of course this guy loses all rights on the kill if he dies, zones, or feign death. This is commonly known. What isnt always known is that when a pet is charmed, the damage list is entirely reset. So if a&nbsp;&nbsp;bard/enchanter/shaman/necro/druid charms a mob, the kill will be given to the guy who will deal the most damage after the charm breaks. All damages done before are not counted. This is very useful for powerlevelers: take a mob down to very low hp for exemple until u see less than half a milimeter or hp left, then uncharm it and let your overbuffed noob finish it with a nuke or raw weapons, or even easier root the mob and give ur noob a damage shield and a rune. An enchanter and a druid can powerlevel very efficiently until level 50 that way.<br>All of this cause Verant allowed any charm class to steal kill all others. Of course charming a mob to steal kill usually lead to a deleted account, but in some places like Karnor some people manage to justify that with bad pathways, mob attacked them, or just "didnt know"...<br>Another thing i wanted to add is about the xp modifier. On kunark you can have 10 more on xp modifier for any zone compared to old game zones. Thus u level faster if u kill mobs from kunark dungeons or outdoor zones than in old zones.<br>One last advice: some mobs in the game have less hp than usual for their levels. Just an exemple: bloodgil goblins underwater in lake of ill omen have about 1300 hp (they require only an e bolt and a winter s roar to die), which is about half the hp of same level mobs from other zones. They are around level 39 and therefore are all blue until 47, and give good xp until 50. If u can get fishbone earrings or rebreathers or anything that allows to breath underwater, u can make excellent xp on them as long as u can pull them one by one or you are a group with a tank and a healer. A caster alone can have a hard time on them because it s underwater and ur spells will get interrupted as soon as ure hit, but with a tank it s the fastest xp ive seen in the game. There are about 10 goblins to pull so u can just kill them non stop.<br>Me and a warrior made 46 to 50 in 16 hours on them, far faster than anything else ive seen in the game (not considering powerleveling of course...)<br>I hope these will help people who are sick of raising alts get them at a decent level easily.<br>I also hope i wont see bards or druids kill stealing almost dead mobs in front of me with the charm trick :-)<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
